
    Police in Limpopo have arrested the wife of a teacher and two other men in connection with his murder in August.Limpopo police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the teacher's wife, 37, her boyfriend, 42, and the alleged hitman, 34, were arrested this week.Daniel Ramaipadi, 53, a teacher and head of department at a local school, was gunned down by unknown men at his home in Ga-Motodi village outside Burgersfort in August. His car was also taken but was later recovered near the scene of the murder.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsveFTY6pxXlUhwGgXwfKJXaHT2QrTnHOF_Ud3Ruw9C2nzcmJvIUXeRJ8AZFqJv9flUX2WwGyUUgPlgSmyqEjHZJDdggJR9kcIJjnT21Y5ZENvsCMr6UpBoRoFvmTLr9V0EgxS0IMWGjEEbBdVWv_nqJh6xau9qDFwwwq2S5YGF3UMIQsHMwBw16nE8wbYXm-BgPCUazkvEew8MX73p4AegVcv-b7qqi16F3AFQhK2KKV68rtTq0ogxxJR0YVOksCDC7RxGhSyb0k_E8s4UPY8rpiMdeLKg\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzNOEIis-NWkiEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
